body:
Please tell us your pip version

pip --version
You're right. Somehow I got 32-bit python... Let me try 64-bit one.

64-bit python got me the error.
> pip3 install onnxruntime-gpu
ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement onnxruntime-gpu (from versions: none)
ERROR: No matching distribution found for onnxruntime-gpu

> pip install onnxruntime_gpu-1.3.0-cp38-cp38-manylinux2010_x86_64.whl
ERROR: onnxruntime_gpu-1.3.0-cp38-cp38-manylinux2010_x86_64.whl is not a supported wheel on this platform.
manylinux2010 is for Linux. You need a Windows one.  But, unfortunately, I'm really sorry, we don't have a Windows GPU package for python 3.8 yet. Could you please downgrade your python to 3.7?
